paternity test is it possible to do a paternity test before the baby is born yes it is possible but there is a very small window of time to do the testing there is one test that can be done between the th and th week of pregnancy and is done by a doctor taking tissue samples from the uterine wall known as the chorionic villi the second test is done between and weeks by amniocentesis since amniocentesis is done by placing a needle through the moms abdomin and taking amniotic fluid out there are some risks involved including a risk of harming the baby miscarriage leaking fluid and bleeding the cost of these tests is between and and is not covered by insurance it also takes alot of planning to get these tests done here is a link to a website about the different procedures http www thelaboroflove com articles can i determine my babys dna while pregnant Prenatal diagnosis In vitro fertilisation Childbirth Spina bifida Pregnancy Abortion Amniotic sac Menstrual cycle Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Urinary incontinence Prostate cancer Endometrial cancer Cystic fibrosis Cephalic disorder Premature birth Breastfeeding Gonorrhoea Diabetic retinopathy Twin Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Aortic dissection Pneumonia Gynecologic hemorrhage Chemical abortion Mesothelioma Medicine Traumatic brain injury Stomach cancer Cancer Breech birth Infertility Turner syndrome Genealogical DNA test Pelvic inflammatory disease Endometriosis Stroke HIV test Ectopic pregnancy Polycystic ovary syndrome Cytomegalovirus Birth weight Genetic fingerprinting Obstetrical hemorrhage Partial-birth abortion Intravenous therapy Condom Hydatidiform mole Becker's muscular dystrophy Pregnancy test HIV Kidney Pregnancy (mammals) Intact dilation and extraction Ebola Androgen insensitivity syndrome Paternity testing Hepatitis C Glycogen storage disease type I Folic acid Gynaecology Cirrhosis Acupuncture Breast cancer Marburg virus Ultraviolet Fertility awareness Bone marrow transplant Uterine fibroids Extreme Program